## 2. Feature Roadmap (UPDATED)

### MVP (Weeks 1–12: Validate Core Loop)
**Goal**: Prove that flexible scheduling (your choice of workflow) solves multi-ministry chaos with 1–2 beta churches. Self-contained operation or ChMS integration.

#### 2.1 People Import & Initial Setup
- **ChMS API integrations** (optional):
  - Planning Center Services: OAuth → pull volunteers, teams, roles, household relationships
  - Breeze: API key → same data pull
  - Rock RMS: API → same data pull
  - Fallback: CSV upload (name, email, phone, ministry, role, household ID)
- **Standalone setup**: Manual entry form (no ChMS needed)
- **Data ownership**: All data stays in VC, nothing required to push back to ChMS

#### 2.2 Ministries & Services Config
- **Admin creates ministry** (e.g., "Worship", "Kids", "Greeters", "Tech"):
  - Display name, color code, description, team lead email
- **Admin creates recurring services** under ministry (e.g., "Sunday 9am", "Sunday 11am", "Wed 7pm"):
  - Frequency (weekly, monthly, custom pattern)
  - Time slot (start, duration)
  - Roles/positions with needed counts (e.g., "2x Band", "1x Sound Tech")
  - Can copy previous service as template
- **Zero ChMS sync required** if using standalone

#### 2.3 Volunteer Availability & Constraints
- **Volunteer portal** (web & PWA):
  - Set blockout dates ("Never available Jan 20–27")
  - Recurring time slot prefs ("Never 8am", "Only weekends")
  - Preferred frequency (e.g., "2x/month", "Max 3 roles/month")
  - Household link ("Serve with spouse", "Never schedule while my kid is in another ministry")
  - Skills/roles available for
- **Admin bulk actions**: Upload 50 volunteers, auto-assign to teams, set default availability

#### 2.4 Workflow Mode Selection (NEW - Your Request)
- **Admin configures preferred workflow** (one-time setup):
  ```
  Mode 1: "Centralized" (Recommended for multi-ministry)
  - Admin auto-drafts entire org schedule (all ministries at once)
  - All team leads review/approve their ministry in parallel
  - Global publish when all approved → all volunteers get emails
  
  Mode 2: "Ministry-First" (Traditional)
  - Each ministry lead generates their own schedule
  - Admin reviews for conflicts only
  - Individual ministry publishes (no global coordination)
  
  Mode 3: "Hybrid"
  - Auto-draft creates ministry templates
  - Leaders tweak independently
  - Admin dashboard shows cross-ministry conflicts (alerts only)
  
  Mode 4: "Self-Service" (SignUpGenius style)
  - Volunteers self-signup for open slots
  - No approval workflow
  ```
- **Default to Mode 1** for MVP; others added week 8–12 if needed

#### 2.5 Auto-Draft Engine (Core Magic)
- **One-click "Auto-Draft Schedule"**:
  - User selects date range (e.g., "Next 8 weeks", "April–May")
  - Engine runs scheduling algorithm:
    - Respects availability & blockouts
    - Honors frequency caps & household conflicts
    - Tries fair distribution (no burnout, no idle volunteers)
    - Prevents skill mismatches
    - Returns draft schedule with conflict flags
- **Flags for review**:
  - Unfilled roles (gaps)
  - Over-booked volunteers
  - Low-confidence assignments
- **Draft matrix view** (rows = volunteers, columns = services, cells = role or blank)

#### 2.6 Team Lead Review & Approval (Flexible)
- **Mode 1 (Centralized)**:
  - Admin sends draft to all team leads (email with deep link)
  - Each lead sees only their ministry's schedule
  - Buttons: "Approve as-is", "Tweak", or "Reject"
  - Can swap volunteers, add someone, remove someone
  - All must approve before admin publishes
- **Mode 2 (Ministry-First)**:
  - Each lead generates independently, publishes individually
  - Admin dashboard shows when conflicts arise
  - Manual conflict resolution

#### 2.7 Global Publish & Volunteer Response (Flexible)
- **Centralized mode**: Admin clicks "Publish" (all leads approved) → bulk email to all volunteers
- **Ministry-first mode**: Each lead publishes independently
- **Volunteer response options**:
  - Web/PWA link: "Accept", "Decline", "Request Substitute"
  - Calendar invite with RSVP (iCal)
  - SMS link (if opted in)
  - In-app response

#### 2.8 Calendar Feeds (NEW - Your Request)
- **Calendar types** (each volunteer/leader can subscribe):
  - Personal: "My Schedule" (volunteer sees only their assignments)
  - Team: "Worship Team Schedule" (lead + team members)
  - Ministry: "Kids Ministry Schedule" (admin + leaders only)
  - Org-wide: "All Ministries" (admin only)
- **iCal feed URLs** (unique per person/team/ministry):
  - Auto-updates on schedule changes
  - Works with Google Calendar, Outlook, Apple Calendar
  - Privacy: public (team), password-protected, invite-only, or private
- **Import path**: Volunteer subscribes to their personal iCal → auto-syncs to phone/calendar

#### 2.9 Reminders (NEW - Your Request - Flexible)
- **Automated reminders** (configurable per volunteer):
  ```
  Email: 48hr + 24hr before service
  SMS: 48hr + 24hr (opt-in, charges Twilio usage)
  Calendar invite: Auto-RSVP request
  In-app: Push notification (PWA)
  None: Opt-out entirely
  ```
- **Admin can configure per role**:
  - Critical roles (sound tech, nursery lead): SMS + email + calendar
  - Regular roles (greeters, ushers): Email only or calendar only
  - Optional roles: No reminders (opt-in only)
- **Volunteer choice**: Can override role defaults in their preferences

#### 2.10 Dashboard & Export
- **Admin dashboard**:
  - Current schedule matrix (4-week rolling view)
  - Fill rate by role (e.g., "Greeters 85% filled")
  - No-show tracker (if ChMS check-ins imported)
  - Declined/pending actions
  - Workflow status (if centralized mode): "Pending approvals: 2/5 team leads"
- **Exports**:
  - CSV (full schedule, volunteer/role)
  - PDF (printable schedule)
  - iCal (personal + team feeds)

#### 2.11 Basic Analytics & Reporting
- **Automated reminders**:
  - 48hr + 24hr before service (configurable)
  - Auto-count responses in real-time
  - Follow-up reminders for non-responders
- **Simple stats**:
  - Total volunteers scheduled
  - Fill rates by role
  - Average times per volunteer
  - No-show rate (if ChMS check-ins available)
  - Response rate (% confirmed after publish)

#### 2.12 MVP Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: React/Next.js (TypeScript), Tailwind CSS, PWA (service workers for offline)
- **Backend**: Node.js/Express or Supabase (PostgreSQL + edge functions)
- **Auth**: Supabase Auth (OAuth for Planning Center/Breeze/Rock, email/password fallback)
- **APIs**: 
  - Planning Center Services API (optional)
  - Breeze API (optional)
  - Rock RMS API (optional)
  - Twilio for SMS
  - iCal generation (native)
- **Hosting**: Vercel (frontend) + Supabase (backend)
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (Supabase)

**MVP Success Metrics**:
- ≥1 beta church live, scheduling 2+ services/week
- ≥100 volunteers in system
- ≥80% auto-draft schedules fixable in <10% manual work
- ≥95% of published schedules get volunteer responses within 24hr
- ≤5% no-show rate (vs. baseline ~15–20%)
- All 4 workflow modes testable (at least 1 working end-to-end)

